  "title": "A Wild Seal Just Turned Completely Purple",
  "script": "A seal turned purple? Rangers at Año Nuevo State Park in California were doing a routine beach check when they spotted it — a full-grown elephant seal, dyed grape-purple from head to flipper. No one poured paint on it. No prank. Marine biologists say it's algae — a natural bloom that can tint a seal's skin when it spends too long resting in the wrong patch of water. The seal itself is completely healthy, just extremely purple, and extremely unbothered about it. Elephant seals already look like nothing else in the ocean — 5,000 pounds, foghorn voice, built like a submarine — and now this one's cosplaying as a grape. Locals are calling it the most goth seal on the California coast. So does the purple wash out, or is this look permanent?",
